23/09/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- NATO has selected the firing field at Novo Selo, the airport at Bezmer and the Burgas port as its possible bases in the country, and negotiations are under way, according to Solomon Passy, who recently served as foreign minister and is now chairman of parliament's foreign policy committee. Speaking Thursday (22 September), he added that if an agreement were reached, 2,000-3,000 US military personnel would be deployed in the country. Passy added that a NATO military delegation is expected to visit Bulgaria in early October to continue talks with the new government. (News.bg, Novinite.com - 22/09/05) 
